0.title: Nix Chad

10.body:
Browser bookmarks. Type: (list of ((bookmark submodule) or (directory submodule))) or (attribute set of ((bookmark submodule) or (directory submodule))) convertible to it Default: [ ] Example: [ { bookmarks = [ { keyword = "nixpkgs"; name = "NixOS Search - Packages"; tags = [ "nix" ]; url = "https://search.nixos.org/packages"; } ]; name = "Nix sites"; toolbar = true; } { title = "Nix Chad"; url = "https://github.com/mstream/nix-chad"; }
] Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/browser.nix>
10.title: chad.browser.bookmarks

11.body: Additional Firefox extensions to be installed for the user. Type: null or (function that evaluates to a(n) list of package) Default: null Example: exts: with exts; [ grammarly ]; Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/browser.nix>
11.title: chad.browser.extraExtensions

12.body: Ideal maximum document’s width measured in number of characters. Type: signed integer Default: 72 Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/editor.nix>
12.title: chad.editor.documentWidth

13.body: Absolute: line numbers counted from the beginning of the document Relative: line numbers counted from the current cursor position Type: one of “absolute”, “relative” Default: "relative" Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/editor.nix>
13.title: chad.editor.lineNumbering

14.body: Tabulation width measured in number of characters. Type: signed integer Default: 2 Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/editor.nix>
14.title: chad.editor.tabWidth

15.body: Additional nixpkgs packages to be accessible for the user. Type: null or (function that evaluates to a(n) list of package) Default: null Example: pkgs: with pkgs; [ cowsay ]; Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/default.nix>
15.title: chad.extraPackages

16.body: A desired font size in tools that have means to set it fixed. Type: signed integer Default: 12 Example: 16 Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/default.nix>
16.title: chad.fontSize

17.body:
Alternative Git identities for selected repositories. Type: list of (submodule) Default: [ ] Example: [ { repositoryPath = "~/work/project-1"; sshKeyPath = "~/.ssh/work_id_rsa"; userEmail = "me@mail.com"; }
] Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/git.nix>
17.title: chad.git.alternativeGitIdentities

18.body: Git repository path. Type: string Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/git.nix>
18.title: chad.git.alternativeGitIdentities.*.repositoryPath

19.body: Path to a SSH private key. Type: string Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/git.nix>
19.title: chad.git.alternativeGitIdentities.*.sshKeyPath

2.body: discoverable key mappings After pressing ? key a window enumerating all contextual key mappings appears.
2.title: Firefox

21.body: An ID of a key to be used for GPG signing by default. This is expected to be different for individuals. The key is not part of this repository and has to be provided manually. Type: null or string Default: null Example: "BE318F09150F6CB0724FFEC0319EE1D7FC029354" Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/gpg.nix>
21.title: chad.gpg.defaultKey

22.body: Holding keys does not make characters being typed repeatedly. Type: boolean Default: true Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/keyboard.nix>
22.title: chad.keyboard.disableKeyRepeat

23.body: Treat Caps Lock key as Escape key. Type: boolean Default: true Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/keyboard.nix>
23.title: chad.keyboard.remapCapsLock

24.body: Treat Left Arrow key as Right Control key. Type: boolean Default: false Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/keyboard.nix>
24.title: chad.keyboard.remapLeftArrow

25.body: Keep windows occupy maximum available share of space on desktop. Type: boolean Default: false Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/manage-windows.nix>
25.title: chad.manageWindows.enable

26.body:
List of application names for which automatic window management should not be performed. It can be figured out using this command: yabai -m query --windows Type: list of (submodule) Default: [ ] Example: [ { app = "^Discord$"; title = ".*Dialog$"; }
] Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/manage-windows.nix>
26.title: chad.manageWindows.exclusions

27.body: Regex for application name. Type: string Example: "^Discord$" Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/manage-windows.nix>
27.title: chad.manageWindows.exclusions.*.app

28.body: Regex for window title. Type: string Default: ".*" Example: ".*Dialog$" Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/manage-windows.nix>
28.title: chad.manageWindows.exclusions.*.title

29.body: Should content scroll opposite to the swipe/roll direction. Type: boolean Default: true Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/mouse.nix>
29.title: chad.mouse.naturalScrollDirection

30.body: Restricts software to Open Source only. Type: boolean Default: true Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/software.nix>
30.title: chad.software.openSourceOnly

31.body: Enables expandable command abbreviations. Type: boolean Default: true Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/terminal.nix>
31.title: chad.terminal.abbreviations.enable

32.body:
An attribute set that maps aliases (the top level attribute names in this option) to abbreviations. Abbreviations are expanded with the longer phrase after they are entered. Type: attribute set of string Default: { } Example: { gco = "git checkout"; l = "less";
} Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/terminal.nix>
32.title: chad.terminal.abbreviations.extraAbbreviations

33.body:
Additional key bindings for terminal emulator. Type: list of (submodule) Default: [ ] Example: [ { chars = "\\u000c"; key = "K"; mods = "Control"; }
] Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/terminal.nix>
33.title: chad.terminal.keyBindings

36.body: Modifier key(s). Type: string Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/terminal.nix>
36.title: chad.terminal.keyBindings.*.mods

37.body:
Additional initialization for ZSH sessions. Type: strings concatenated with “\n” Default: "" Example: '' export VAR1=val1 export VAR2=val2
'' Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/terminal.nix>
37.title: chad.terminal.zshInitExtra

38.body:
A list of desirect directories to be created in the home directory of the user. It is up to the user to provide the contents of these directories. Type: list of string Default: [ ] Example: [ "Development/exercises" "Development/presentations" "Development/projects"
] Declared by: <nix-chad/modules/darwin/chad/user.nix>
38.title: chad.user.homeDirectories

42.body: clA - Comment add at the end of line clO - Comment add line above clo - Comment add line below cb - Comment block operator-pending cl - Comment line operator-pending ctb - Comment toggle block ctl - Comment toggle line
42.title: Comment

43.body: tf - Directory tree focus tt - Directory tree toggle
43.title: Directory Tree

44.body: fd - Find definitions ff - Find files fgb - Find Git branches fgc - Find Git commits fgl - Find Git local changes fgs - Find Git stashed changes fi - Find implementations fvb - Find Vim buffers fvc - Find Vim commands fvh - Find Vim help topics fw - Find words across files
44.title: Find

45.body: gD - Go to declaration gd - Go to definition gi - Go to implementation g] - Go to next problem g[ - Go to previous problem
45.title: Go To

46.body: <ESC> - Cancels current selection or mode. <C-j> - Move to window on the bottom <C-h> - Move to window on the left <C-l> - Move to window on the right <C-k> - Move to window on the top <C-d> - Sroll content down <C-u> - Scroll content up <C-n> - Select next item on a list <C-p> - Select previous item on a list \- Show key mappings K - Show information about the symbol under the cursor <TAB> - switch to next tab <S-TAB> - switch to previous tab
46.title: Miscellaneous
